cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper deals with machine learning models and their ability to generalize to unseen domains. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of adversarial examples, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper proposes a data-dependent regularization scheme, which is related to neural networks (cs.NE).
